<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Wreathe" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Wreathe,</orth> to twine; to fold: <cit><quote>an adder --d up in fatal folds,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 879" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 879</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to w. your arms,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 1, 19</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.135" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 135</bibl>. <cit><quote>about his neck a snake had --d itself,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.109" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 109</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>each --d in the other's arms,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 25</bibl></cit>. cf. <emph>Sorrow-wreathen.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>